Aran island ferry’s is 5 minutes drive. Horse riding and scenic walks around the surrounding countryside. Doolin Caves 2 minutes drive. Pitch and putt 5 minutes drive. Golf course in lahinch is 20 minutes drive. Offering a luxury four star Bed & Breakfast with free WiFi. located just outside Doolin. From our Bed & Breakfast you have a wonderful view of the bay. At Glasha Meadows we offer you peaceful accommodation and the comforts of our spacious bedrooms and bathrooms. We offer 6 spacious bedrooms En-suite Bathrooms, 2 doubles, 1 triple with 3 singles beds, 1 twin with 2 beds, 2 family rooms with 1 double and 2 singles. All our rooms are well heated and on the ground floor. Rooms are equipped with tea & coffee making facilities and TV. We also have a lounge, where you can relax and read about the local area. Main attractions include: Doolin Caves, Cliffs of Moher, The Burren, The Aran Islands, Irish traditional music in the local pubs, Doolin pitch and putt course, close to beaches, Mountain View horse riding centre.

Hello, we are Tony and Joanne Burke owners of Burkedale House for 19 years. We bought it after we moved to Ireland in 2001. Tony is originally from Dublin and Joanne from Oxford. We met over 30 years ago in London. We wanted our children, Naomi & Hamish to be educated in Ireland hence the move to Clare in 2001. The proximity to Shannon Airport was key in our choice of location as Tony, an IT Consultant, commuted for work. Tony was familiar with the county from his rock climbing days and Joanne was soon to fall in love with its diversity. When the children flew the nest and went to university in the UK we decided to head back to the UK too. We wanted other people to enjoy the spectacular views from the house and relax in its comfortable surroundings and began our Airbnb journey. After 6 years back in the UK Joanne retired from her nursing career and we returned to Burkedale House and bought the cottage at the end of the garden. 6 months was spent renovating the 100 year old traditional Irish cottage before welcoming our first guests in April 2018. At the same time we started to offer B&B in the house. We also had a new addition to the family, our border collie, Bali who is a real hit with the guests. Last year we were adopted by Hermione a black and white cat who thought this was a nice place to live! We could not be more delighted with the success of the business and love welcoming guests from around the world. For 2020 we have added our newly renovated Garden Suite, self catering accommodation for 2 people. We of course still have the cottage and 1 B&B room, ( we are not currently offering B&B due to Covid-19) In addition to running the accommodation we are both Nordic Walking instructors working through our sister company Nordic Fitness Ireland We can arrange learn to Nordic Walk courses and guided or self guided walks for our guests ( booking and additional cost required). We always enjoy the 5k circular walk / run from the house round to the monastery and Dysert O’Dea Castle. We love to travel and have visited many places around the world memories of which can be seen on our numerous fridge magnets and landscape photos around the house, and world map in the Garden Suite. We hope you enjoy Burkedale House & Cottage as much as we do.

Irish Landmark is a non-profit organisation that finds interesting and unusual properties that are in need of conservation, and we give them new life. Since 1992, we’ve been turning historic buildings into truly special self-catering holiday accommodation. Our properties range from lighthouses and schoolhouses, to castles and gate lodges. As an educational charity, our primary aim is to conserve and sustain iconic buildings. That’s why Irish Landmark properties are living buildings, not museum settings. Irish Landmark always respects the history and architectural integrity of the structures we conserve, but we also ensure they have all the contemporary comforts you want in a holiday home.

A fully restored Pub and residence ideally located on Main Street , Ennistymon . This beautiful house offers four bedrooms over three floors , sympathetically restored to retain the old timber bar where friends traditionally gathered to share in conversation over a whisky or a pint. The property offers two full bathrooms , a grand parlor with original fireplace , fully stocked kitchen and of course a warm stove in the hearth .The three story building is set on a full cellar and overlooks the historic Falls Hotel to the rear with the crashing power of the Falls themselves only a short stroll from the house (Website hidden by Airbnb) Haran’s is convenient located a stones throw from Eugene’s Bar , a must see for any visitor to Ennistymon,and the award winning coffee shop The Cheese Press , which boasts the best cheese toasty in the country according to the Irish Times. Across the street visitors will find Little Fox, one of the seven of the Irish Times’ Great out-of-the places to Eat’ in 2019 . Ennistymon oozes a classic country charm , offering a collection of cafes , a health food shop, a creperie , second hand shops ,music shops , a traditional woolen weaver and plenty of pubs with traditional Irish music . On Saturday morning’s locals muse around the farmers market and every morning and every evening the crows take up position on the roof tops to discuss the business of the da (Website hidden by Airbnb) Ennistymon is a wonderful base to explore Co Clare , with the Cliffs of Moher just 14km away and the famous surf beach at Lahinch only 3km .The fish restaurants and bars at Liscannor are just 8km from Haran’s and Lisdoonvarna , Fanore , Ballyvaughan ,Kilfenora ,Miltown Malbay , Doonbeg , Kilkee and Kilrush are all within easy driving distanc (Website hidden by Airbnb) Haran’s will be your quiet , comfortable yet stylish retreat to arrive home to after a busy day exploring the great majestic lunar landscape of the Burren and all the dramatic outdoor delights of County Clare .

Situated in the heart of Dublin, Dublin Central Suites feature 22 elegantly furnished self-catering apartments with free WiFi, fully equipped kitchen, a dining area and a 24 hour reception desk. Located just off Dorset Street (N1), the serviced apartments are less than 15 minutes’ (10km) drive from Dublin Airport and 10 minutes’ walk from Dublin’s main shopping and entertainment streets including Henry Street and Grafton Street which are ideal places to visit for the shopaholics. The nearest LUAS (Tram) stop at Parnell Square is also less than 10 minutes’ walk (900m) away. Football fans will find themselves in the close proximity of Croke Park which is only 8 minutes’ walk (700m) away. Airlink Express bus stop is also down the road from the apartments on Lower Gardiner Street. All apartments are fitted with large LED Smart TVs with large selection of satellite TV channels and feature a digital safe, fridge/freezer, kettle, toaster, cooker and a work desk. Private bathrooms feature power showers and free toiletries. Washing machines are available on site. Most apartments feature sofa beds and are ideal for families, larger groups or business travellers who seek privacy and comfort of home only an apartment can offer. There are no parking spaces at the property however, there is ample street parking and a large car park is only 2 minutes’ drive away. The car park costs €15 per day.

You'll find Generator Dublin in the hip Smithfield neighbourhood; adjacent to the Jameson Distillery and just a short walk from Temple Bar. Our Dublin hotel features open social spaces and is equipped with a café/restaurant and a bar on-site. With its reclaimed wood, exposed brickwork and original stonework, the place has an unruffled, industrial feel. Our Dublin hostel even boasts a jacuzzi suite; a shared room that comes with a hot tub! It’s ideal for a girls’ or boys’ weekend away – especially if you’re after a more luxurious budget hotel experience in Dublin. From the Irish music belting out of the pubs in Temple Bar to the elegant splendour of Georgian terraces and squares, the city has many fascinating faces – every one of them ready to greet you with a welcoming smile and a pint of Guinness.

CURRENT MISSION Live the life now, check the world and have as much fun as I can. ABOUT ME A friendly funny guy, not too noisy, not too quiet. Always ready for a beer or to help with a puncture! PHILOSOPHY Live as the hummingbird story- One day a terrible fire broke out in a forest - a huge woodlands was suddenly engulfed by a raging wild fire. Frightened, all the animals fled their homes and ran out of the forest. As they came to the edge of a stream they stopped to watch the fire and they were feeling very discouraged and powerless. They were all bemoaning the destruction of their homes. Every one of them thought there was nothing they could do about the fire, except for one little hummingbird. This particular hummingbird decided it would do something. It swooped into the stream and picked up a few drops of water and went into the forest and put them on the fire. Then it went back to the stream and did it again, and it kept going back, again and again and again. All the other animals watched in disbelief; some tried to discourage the hummingbird with comments like, "Don't bother, it is too much, you are too little, your wings will burn, your beak is too tiny, it’s only a drop, you can't put out this fire." And as the animals stood around disparaging the little bird’s efforts, the bird noticed how hopeless and forlorn they looked. Then one of the animals shouted out and challenged the hummingbird in a mocking voice, "What do you think you are doing?" And the hummingbird, without wasting time or losing a beat, looked back and said, "I am doing what I can." Why to use bnb Travel is one of my loves in life, and I think that AirBnB is one of the best options to do it. For me a trip is not to travel somewhere and take some pictures. I want to know people, do the things people do where I travel and learn another ways of life!! Interests Live music, go out for a beer, enjoy a good meal and spend as much time as I can with my friends! I'm trying to learn how to play the guitar but I just manage to play some songs.. anyway it's cool that way!

Plenty of shops nearby too like (Hidden by Airbnb) Fresh, Spar, Marks and Spencer and Tesco. Arriving by plane in Dublin is very easy to reach to our place. At the Airport you go to the bus stop number (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , you take the bus number 41 for about 36 minutes (30 stops) to Abbey Street (Irish Life Mall stop), walk for about 9 minutes (700 metres) then you are in front of the apartment complex. The journey (including waiting time) will take around 55 minutes. Another option is the Airlink bus (costs €6 one way or €10 return). At the Airport you go to bus stop number (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , you take the bus number 747 for about 35 minutes (5 stops) to Common Street, Connolly Car Park, walk for 3 minutes (203 metres) then you are in front of the apartment complex.
